#### **Day 33: Introduction to CSS (Styling)**
```markdown
# Day 33: Styling with CSS - Selectors and Colors

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. Three ways to add CSS: Inline, Internal, External.
2. CSS Selectors: Element, ID (`#`), Class (`.`).
3. Colors (Hex codes, RGB) and Backgrounds.
4. Font properties (`font-family`, `font-weight`).

**Learning Summary:**
HTML provides the structure, but CSS provides the style. Today I learned how to link a `.css` file to my HTML. The most important concept was "Selectors"â€”how to target specific elements to style them. I learned that ID selectors are unique, while Class selectors can be reused on multiple elements.

**Code Snippet:**
```css
/* style.css */

/* Element Selector */
body {
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
}

/* Class Selector (Reusable) */
.highlight {
    color: white;
    background-color: tomato;
    padding: 5px;
}

/* ID Selector (Unique) */
#main-header {
    text-align: center;
    color: #333;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #333;
}
